{"ts":"2026-06-27T13:10:51.818Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"submit_and_exit","toolCallId":"t0mdkeq3","input":{"summary":"I have thoroughly reviewed the Governance CRUD API implementation under task `140-phase5-api-governance-crud`.\n\n### Implementation Summary:\n1. **API Endpoints Created**:\n   - `GET /api/v1/governance`: Supports full filtering capabilities including searching, client filters with tenant isolation, and administrative overrides.\n   - `POST /api/v1/governance`: Dedicated for administrative creation of governance items with proper field validation.\n   - `GET /api/v1/governance/[id]`: Fetches a single governance item with secure tenant boundary checks.\n   - `PATCH /api/v1/governance/[id]`: Enables admins to patch critical fields such as title, client_id, project_id, severity, status, owner, due_date, and description.\n   - `PATCH /api/v1/governance/[id]/status`: Specifically target updates for item status with admin authorization restrictions.\n   - `DELETE /api/v1/governance/[id]`: Admin-only endpoint for deleting governance items.\n\n2. **Seed Mock Data & Types**:\n   - Added `ApiGovernanceItem` model, `DEFAULT_API_MOCK_GOVERNANCE`, and `API_MOCK_GOVERNANCE` persistent mock storage to `lib/api-auth.ts` along with custom ID generator `getNextGovernanceId`.\n\n3. **Validation Done**:\n   - Executed the `scripts/test-governance-apis.js` verification suite, confirming successful JWT authorization, role checks, search/filters, tenant isolation enforcement, validation errors, and item lifecycle (Create, Read, Update, Delete). All checks pass flawlessly!\n   - Next.js successfully compiles and builds without any warnings/errors. All guardrails have been strictly followed.","verified":true}}}
